{"by":"otterley","id":47774165,"kids":[47774273,47774198,47774192],"parent":47772012,"text":"Why do people consistently and falsely believe that they have privacy in public settings? You are literally out in public. If you don&#x27;t want your behavior in public to be observed, then either don&#x27;t behave in such a way that you wouldn&#x27;t want observed, or stay home.<p>UPDATE: don&#x27;t conflate stalking with observation. These are not the same. You can observe, but you cannot intimidate.","time":1776221767,"type":"comment"}